%3E1.%20Bill%20Ackman%2C%20billionaire%20CEO%20of%20Pershing%20Square%2C%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FBillAckman%2Fstatus%2F1710784469853233218%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EX%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhy%20did%20Hamas%20invade%20Israel%20last%20night%3F%20Because%20the%20United%20States%20has%20consistently%20not%20kept%20its%20word%20on%20its%20foreign%20policy%20commitments%20and%20we%20look%20very%20weak.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTerrorism%20loves%20a%20leadership%20vacuum%20and%20we%20have%20created%20one.%20The%20world%20has%20become%20a%20much%20more%20dangerous%20place%20because%20we%20have%20not%20kept%20our%20word.%20%C2%A0This%20needs%20to%20stop%20now%20or%2C%20dare%20I%20say%2C%20hell%20is%20coming.%20The%20world%20is%20a%20much%20safer%20place%20when%20the%20US%20leads%2C%20and%20it%20quickly%20can%20become%20a%20living%20hell%20when%20we%20fail%20to%20do%20so.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cu%3E2.%20Chamath%20Palihapitiya%2C%20billionaire%20CEO%20of%20Social%20Capital%2C%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fchamath%2Fstatus%2F1710890763205406980%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EX%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBiden%20drained%20the%20SPR%20to%20help%20push%20down%20US%20CPI%20when%20oil%20looked%20like%20it%20was%20going%20to%20%24100.%20How%20does%20oil%20not%20spike%20again%20now%20on%20the%20back%20of%20two%20hot%20wars%20(Israel-Hamas%20and%20Russia-Ukraine)%20and%20a%201.5M%20barrel%20production%20cut%20by%20OPEC%20with%20an%20SPR%20that%20is%20at%20the%20same%20level%20it%20was%20in%20the%20mid%201980s%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20inflation%20then%20spikes%20back%20up%2C%20what%20does%20the%20Fed%20do%3F%20The%20Fed%20is%20already%20in%20a%20game%20of%20chicken%20with%20the%20bond%20market%20and%20is%20under%20a%20lot%20of%20pressure%20to%20do%20no%20harm%20and%20ideally%20start%20the%20cutting%20cycle%20soon.%20This%20would%20make%20that%20path%20much%20less%20likely.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20if%20all%20of%20these%20events%20roil%20the%20capital%20markets%20and%20potentially%20triggers%20a%20recession%2C%20the%20establishment%20version%20of%20'the%20solution'%20in%20Washington%20will%20regain%20favor.%20Their%20intentions%20have%20always%20been%20clear%3A%20escalate%20our%20involvement%20abroad%20as%20a%20source%20of%20US%20pride%2C%20growth%20and%20hegemony.%20This%20will%20mean%20getting%20deeper%20into%20Russia-Ukraine%20and%20now%20potentially%20Israel-Hamas.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cu%3E3.%20Ed%20Yardeni%2C%20president%20of%20Yardeni%20Research%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-10-08%2Fglobal-markets-face-new-geopolitical-risk-view-oil-as-guidepost%3FleadSource%3Duverify%2520wall%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20Bloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGeopolitical%20crises%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20have%20usually%20caused%20oil%20prices%20to%20rise%20and%20stock%20prices%20to%20fall.%20Much%20will%20depend%20on%20whether%20the%20crisis%20turns%20out%20to%20be%20another%20short-term%20flare-up%20or%20something%20much%20bigger%20like%20a%20war%20between%20Israel%20and%20Iran.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cu%3E4.%20Russ%20Mould%2C%20investment%20director%20of%20AJ%20Bell%2C%20in%20a%20morning%20note%3A%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20wider%20risk%20is%20that%20a%20sustained%20increase%20in%20oil%20prices%20would%20act%20as%20a%20renewed%20inflationary%20pressure%20and%20further%20underpin%20the%20higher%20rates%20for%20longer%20message%20which%20investors%20in%20the%20equity%20and%20bond%20markets%20seem%20to%20be%20belatedly%20coming%20to%20terms%20with.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cu%3E5.%20Guillermo%20Santos%2C%20head%20of%20strategy%20at%20iCapital%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-10-08%2Fglobal-markets-face-new-geopolitical-risk-view-oil-as-guidepost%3FleadSource%3Duverify%2520wall%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20Bloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20evident%20that%20any%20extension%20of%20this%20to%20oil-producing%20countries%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%20in%20the%20lead%2C%20could%20make%20the%20price%20of%20crude%20oil%20more%20expensive%20with%20negative%20inflationary%20effects%20for%20the%20West%20and%20would%20mean%20higher%20rates%20for%20longer%20and%20falling%20stock%20markets%20if%20the%20above%20caused%20a%20recession.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cu%3E6.%20Anthi%20Tsouvali%2C%20multi-asset%20strategist%20at%20State%20Street%20Global%20Markets%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-10-08%2Fglobal-markets-face-new-geopolitical-risk-view-oil-as-guidepost%3FleadSource%3Duverify%2520wall%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20Bloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20timing%20of%20the%20conflict%20could%20not%20have%20been%20worse%20given%20the%20talks%20between%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20Israel.%20A%20conflict%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20has%20obvious%20implication%20in%20oil%20prices.%20Markets%20will%20worry%20about%20higher%20energy%20prices%20and%20since%20we%20are%20already%20in%20a%20risk-off%20environment%2C%20that%20could%20push%20equity%20markets%20lower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEquity%20markets%20should%20see%20through%20this%20in%20terms%20of%20repricing%20risky%20assets%20but%20sentiment%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20stay%20subdued%20for%20longer%20as%20the%20market%20narrative%20shifts%20from%20soft%20landing%20to%20higher-for-longer%20and%20in%20the%20long%20run%20that%20would%20be%20bad%20for%20equity%20markets.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20h