20on%20legacy%20admissions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20especially%20at%20Harvard%2C%20which%20was%20a%20defendant%20in%20one%20of%20the%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvards-legacy-admission-standards-civil-rights-complaint-scotus-affirmative-action-2023-7%5C%22%3EHarvard%20and%20other%20high-status%20schools%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20valued%20legacy%20students%2C%20it's%20unlikely%20they%20will%20give%20up%20the%20practice%20easily%2C%20even%20with%20the%20Department%20of%20Education%20investigating%20the%20practice.%20These%20institutions%20say%20legacy%20admissions%20help%20foster%20relationships%20with%20alumni%20and%20promote%20an%20intergenerational%20community.%20But%20experts%20told%20me%20there%20is%20an%20underlying%20justification%3A%20money.%20Schools%20might%20believe%20that%20giving%20preference%20to%20children%20of%20alumni%20would%20prompt%20donations%20down%20the%20road.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20rationale%2C%20however%2C%20is%20coming%20under%20scrutiny.%20The%20explosion%20of%20endowments%20at%20elite%20colleges%20has%20allowed%20many%20forward-looking%20schools%20to%20drop%20their%20legacy%20preference%20with%20no%20signs%20of%20financial%20suffering.%20By%20clinging%20to%20legacy%20admissions%2C%20colleges%20are%20not%20only%20undermining%20claims%20of%20advancing%20equality%20but%20may%20be%20shooting%20themselves%20in%20the%20financial%20foot.%20By%20prioritizing%20the%20children%20of%20alumni%2C%20they're%20casting%20aside%20a%20more%20diverse%20pool%20of%20qualified%20applicants%20who%20may%20be%20even%20more%20apt%20to%20donate%20down%20the%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLegacy%20harms%20almost%20all%20Americans%20unless%20you%20are%20legacy%2C%26quot%3B%20James%20Murphy%2C%20the%20deputy%20director%20of%20higher-education%20policy%20at%20nonprofit%20Education%20Reform%20Now%20%E2%80%94%20which%20advocates%20for%20equality%20in%20education%20%E2%80%94%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20who's%20a%20legacy%3F%20It's%20a%20benefit%20that%20goes%20to%20the%20wealthiest%20people%20in%20the%20country%20and%20harms%20everybody%20else.%20So%20why%20do%20we%20even%20have%20it%20at%20this%20point%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'A%20weak%20and%20sad%20excuse'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20legacy%20preference%20has%20always%20been%20a%20dance%20of%20public%20intentions%20and%20private%20subtext.%20When%20the%20practice%20started%20in%20the%201920s%2C%20schools%20said%20they%20were%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F23055549%3Fread-now%3D1%26seq%3D9%23page_scan_tab_contents%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esimply%20seeking%20applicants%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20demonstrated%20%26quot%3Bgood%20character%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bsolidarity.%26quot%3B%20In%20reality%2C%20Richard%20Kahlenberg%2C%20a%20nonresident%20scholar%20at%20Georgetown%20University%20who%20was%20an%20expert%20witness%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20affirmative-action%20cases%2C%20told%20me%2C%20legacy%20preferences%20were%20actually%20designed%20to%20restrict%20the%20number%20of%20Jewish%20students%20who%20were%20admitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20rationales%20for%20preserving%20legacy%20admissions%20have%20evolved%2C%20the%20propensity%20to%20obfuscate%20them%20hasn't.%20For%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Feducation%2F2023%2F07%2F16%2Flegacy-college-admissions-affirmative-action%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eschools%20that%20still%20consider%20legacy%20status%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20100%20as%20of%20July%2C%20by%20one%20count%20%E2%80%94%20the%20stated%20rationale%20for%20the%20practice%20is%20usually%20a%20desire%20to%20%26quot%3Bstay%20connected%26quot%3B%20with%20alumni.%20Princeton%20University's%20president%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fnews%2Fgrade-point%2Fwp%2F2017%2F10%2F23%2Fhow-a-hidden-minority-of-the-disadvantaged-gained-strength-at-princeton%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChristopher%20Eisgruber%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20The%20Washington%20Post%20in%202017%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20ties%20back%20to%20earlier%20generations%20add%20something%20special%20to%20our%20community.%26quot%3B%20In%20a%202018%20report%2C%20Harvard's%20Committee%20to%20Study%20Race-Neutral%20Alternatives%20said%20that%20considering%20alumni%20relationships%20in%20admissions%20%26quot%3Bhelps%20to%20cement%20strong%20bonds%20between%20the%20university%20and%20its%20alumni.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20Ethan%20Poskanzer%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Colorado%20at%20Boulder%2C%20told%20me%2C%20legacies%20also%20%26quot%3Bcome%20from%20families%20that%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20flagged%20as%20high%20potential%20donors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20less%20likely%20to%20apply%20for%20financial%20aid%20and%20just%20pay%20more%20tuition%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20they%20also%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20attend%20the%20college%20if%20they%20are%20admitted%2C%20so%20they're%20more%20likely%20to%20accept%20their%20offers%2C%20which%20means%20a%20stabler%20stream%20of%20tuition%20for%20the%20college.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELoath%20as%20these%20schools%20are%20to%20be%20so%20explicit%2C%20their%20financial%20motivations%20aren't%20exactly%20kept%20secret.%20That%20same%202018%20Harvard%20report%20noted%20that%20%26quot%3BHarvard%20alumni%20also%20offer%20generous%20financial%20support%20to%20their%20alma%20mater%26quot%3B%20and%20described%20their%20donations%20as%20%26quot%3Bessential%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20university's%20operations.%20The%20report%20continued%20that%20%26quot%3Balthough%20alumni%20support%20Harvard%20for%20many%20reasons%2C%20the%20committee%20is%20concerned%20that%20eliminating%20any%20consideration%20of%20whether%20an%20applicant's%20parent%20attended%20Harvard%20or%20Radcliffe%20would%20diminish%20this%20vital%20sense%20of%20engagement%20and%20support.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EIf%20your%20giving%20goes%20down%20just%20because%20you%20removed%20this%20quid%20pro%20quo%20for%20alumni%2C%20then%2C%20gosh%2C%20you're%20not%20doing%20a%20great%20job%20of%20cultivating%20relationships%20with%20alumni%2C%20right%3F%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20have%20echoed%20these%20sentiments%20more%20recently.%20In%20an%20op-ed%20article%20for%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20this%20past%20summer%2C%20James%20Hankins%2C%20a%20history%20professor%20at%20Harvard%2C%20argued%20that%20wealthy%20schools%20like%20Harvard%20and%20Princeton%20%26quot%3Bcan't%20begin%20to%20maintain%20their%20operations%20on%20tuition%20alone%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20alumni%20generosity%20had%20largely%20kept%20those%20schools%20afloat.%20He%20also%20referred%20to%20the%20risk%20of%20relying%20on%20donations%20from%20%26quot%3Bforeign%20donors%20and%20corporations%26quot%3B%20who%20might%20be%20seeking%20political%20influence%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20%26quot%3Bwealthy%20alumni%20%E2%80%94%20legacies%20themselves%20and%20the%20hopeful%20parents%20of%20legacies%20%E2%80%94%20who%20know%20and%20love%20the%20institution%20and%20want%20to%20show%20their%20loyalty.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMurphy%20called%20this%20%26quot%3Ba%20weak%20and%20sad%20excuse%26quot%3B%20to%20maintain%20legacy%20admissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20your%20giving%20goes%20down%20just%20because%20you%20removed%20this%20quid%20pro%20quo%20for%20alumni%2C%20then%2C%20gosh%2C%20you're%20not%20doing%20a%20great%20job%20of%20cultivating%20relationships%20with%20alumni%2C%20right%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIf%20it's%20really%20just%20about%20an%20exchange%2C%20you%20don't%20have%20a%20strong%20alumni%20relationship.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%2C%20the%20sheer%20size%20of%20these%20schools'%20financial%20chests%20makes%20it%20hard%20to%20argue%20that%20alumni%20donations%20are%20necessary%20to%20survive.%20Harvard%20has%20the%20biggest%20college%20endowment%20in%20the%20US%2C%20totaling%20over%20%2450%20billion%2C%20and%20alumni%20donations%20don't%20make%20up%20a%20majority%20of%20its%20revenue.%20While%20Harvard%20has%20not%20publicly%20provided%20an%20exact%20breakdown%20of%20how%20much%20money%20it%20gets%20in%20alumni%20gifts%2C%20it%20reported%20earning%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-harvard-endowment-legacy-admissions-alumni-funding-2023-7%5C%22%3E45%25%20of%20its%20revenue%20in%20its%202022%20fiscal%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20philanthropy%2C%20which%20is%20the%20category%20that%20includes%20gifts%20from%20donors%20and%20alumni.%20It's%20unclear%20how%20big%20of%20a%20role%20alumni%20donations%20play%20within%20that%20category%2C%20but%20Harvard%20has%20largely%20grown%20its%20financial%20might%20on%20the%20back%20of%20investments%20%E2%80%94%20its%20private-equity%20investments%2C%20a%20third%20of%20the%20school's%20total%20portfolio%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2021%2F10%2F15%2Fbusiness%2Fdealbook%2Fcollege-endowment-funds-harvard.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturned%2077%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021%20with%20a%20slight%20decline%20in%202022.%20Princeton%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20said%20it%20raised%20%24140%20million%20in%20unrestricted%20annual%20giving%20and%20spendable%20restricted%20gifts%2C%20including%20alumni%20donations%20in%202022%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that%20money%20was%20just%200.4%25%20of%20its%20total%20endowment%20of%20%2435%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225232%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Harvard%20University%20campus%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c2bca8048ff200190c123a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222615%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20campus%20of%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20and%20Harvard%20University%2C%20July%2026%2C%202016%20in%20Boston%2C%20Massachusetts.%20Harvard%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20prestigious%20business%20schools%20in%20the%20world%2C%20emphasizes%20the%20case%20method%20in%20the%20classroom%3Cp%3EBrooks%20Kraft%2FCorbis%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Harvard%20and%20the%20other%20schools%20clinging%20to%20legacy%20status%20got%20rid%20of%20the%20practice%2C%20there's%20little%20evidence%20that%20alumni%20donations%20would%20dry%20up.%20Murphy%20noted%20that%20MIT%20had%20never%20considered%20legacy%2C%20and%20its%20endowment%20is%20nearly%20%2425%20billion%2C%20while%20the%20University%20of%20Texas%20System%20has%20built%20a%20%2430%20billion%20endowment%20while%20operating%20under%20a%20state%20ban%20on%20legacy%20preference%20in%20public%20schools.%20In%20fact%2C%20a%202010%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fs3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com%2Fproduction.tcf.org%2Fapp%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F03%2F08201915%2F2010-09-15-chapter_5.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20researchers%20at%20The%20Century%20Foundation%20of%20100%20top%20colleges%20also%20found%20%26quot%3Bno%20statistically%20significant%20evidence%20that%20legacy%20preferences%20impact%20total%20alumni%20giving.%26quot%3B%20When%20Amherst%20ditched%20legacy%20from%20its%20admissions%20process%20in%202021%2C%20it%20acknowledged%20it%20would%20be%20just%20fine%20financially%20without%20legacies%2C%20with%20its%20president%20Biddy%20Martin%20saying%20its%20%243.8%20billion%20endowment%20allowed%20the%20school%20to%20make%20this%20decision.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20doing%20what%20we're%20doing%20because%20we%20can%2C%20and%20because%20we%20should%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Gabrielle%20Starr%2C%20the%20president%20of%20Pomona%20College%20%E2%80%94%20which%20got%20rid%20of%20legacy%20admissions%20in%202017%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2023%2F09%2F25%2Fbusiness%2Flegacy-admissions-curious-consumer%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealso%20told%20CNN%20in%20a%20story%20this%20year%20that%20alumni%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20not%20stopped%20giving%20since%20the%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEnding%20legacy%20admissions%20could%20even%20end%20up%20strengthening%20the%20financial%20position%20of%20the%20schools.%20Research%20by%20the%20Council%20for%20Advancement%20and%20Support%20of%20Education%20found%20that%2076%25%20of%20all%20money%20donated%20to%20higher-education%20institutions%20in%20the%202021-2022%20school%20year%20came%20from%20non-alumni%20donors%20%E2%80%94%20mainly%20from%20corporations%20and%20large%20organizations.%20If%20those%20big%20donors%20are%20convinced%20that%20eliminating%20legacy%20consideration%20is%20in%20the%20best%20interests%20of%20the%20school%20and%20students%2C%20Murphy%20said%2C%20it%20could%20lead%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20giving.%20Murphy%20also%20suggested%20that%20some%20alumni%20might%20become%20even%20more%20excited%20to%20donate%20to%20a%20school%20viewed%20as%20having%20made%20%26quot%3Bthe%20college%20admissions%20process%20a%20little%20fairer.%26quot%3B%20And%2C%20in%20theory%2C%20by%20opening%20up%20the%20pool%20of%20potential%20alumni%20instead%20of%20relying%20on%20the%20same%20family%20trees%2C%20colleges%20have%20the%20chance%20to%20have%20the%20next%20mega-donor%20or%20corporate%20titan%20pass%20through%20their%20halls.%20When%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwesleyan-university-is-getting-rid-of-legacy-admissions-2023-7%5C%22%3EWesleyan%20University%20announced%20in%20July%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20was%20dropping%20legacy%20admissions%2C%20its%20president%2C%20Michael%20Roth%2C%20said%20he%20believed%20that%20the%20move%20could%20actually%20lead%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20alumni%20donations.%20%26quot%3BI%20believe%20I%20can%20raise%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20from%20Wesleyan%20alums%20who%20are%20genuinely%20pleased%20to%20support%20an%20institution%20that's%20aligned%20with%20their%20values%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Inside%20Higher%20Ed%2C%20an%20industry%20magazine%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insidehighered.com%2Fnews%2Fadmissions%2Ftraditional-age%2F2023%2F07%2F31%2Fwesleyan-president-discusses-why-he-ended-legacy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20an%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'It's%20embarrassing%20for%20institutions'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELegacy%20admissions%20aren't%20enough%20to%20keep%20a%20school%20financially%20afloat%2C%20but%20they%20are%20good%20for%20one%20thing%3A%20getting%20already%20wealthy%20kids%20into%20college.%20Research%20published%20this%20year%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopportunityinsights.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FCollegeAdmissions_Paper.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeconomists%20from%20Harvard%20and%20Brown%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20children%20from%20families%20in%20the%20top%201%25%20were%20%26quot%3Bmore%20than%20twice%20as%20likely%26quot%3B%20to%20attend%20an%20Ivy%20League%20school%20or%20Stanford%2C%20MIT%2C%20Duke%2C%20and%20University%20of%20Chicago%20as%20children%20from%20middle-class%20families%20who%20had%20comparable%20scores%20on%20standardized%20tests%20%E2%80%94%20they%20concluded%2046%25%20of%20this%20%26quot%3Badmissions%20advantage%26quot%3B%20came%20from%20legacy%20preference.%20And%20a%20research%20paper%20authorized%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1177%2F00031224221122889%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPoskanzer%20and%20MIT's%20Emilio%20Castilla%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20%26quot%3Blegacies%20are%20neither%20more%20qualified%20applicants%20nor%20better%20students%20academically.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUniversities%20will%20say%20they're%20a%20mere%20tiebreaker%2C%20a%20minor%20factor%2C%20and%20all%20the%20careful%20research%20that's%20been%20done%20suggests%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20it's%20a%20very%20large%20preference.%20It%20makes%20a%20big%20difference%20in%20the%20makeup%20of%20the%20student%20bodies%2C%26quot%3B%20Kahlenberg%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20cases%20involving%20Harvard%20and%20the%20University%20of%20North%20Carolina%2C%20both%20schools%20gave%20a%20larger%20preference%20to%20legacy%20students.%20%26quot%3BSo%20in%20essence%2C%20affirmative%20action%20for%20the%20wealthy%20and%20for%20disproportionately%20white%20students%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EI%20believe%20I%20can%20raise%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20from%20Wesleyan%20alums%20who%20are%20genuinely%20pleased%20to%20support%20an%20institution%20that's%20aligned%20with%20their%20values%3C%2Fq%3E%20%3Ccite%3EMichael%20Roth%2C%20Wesleyan%20president%3C%2Fcite%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20very%20preference%20undermines%20schools'%20diversity%20pledges.%20Following%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20decision%2C%20Harvard%20said%20it%20would%20continue%20to%20admit%20students%20who%20reflect%20%26quot%3Bmultiple%20facets%20of%20human%20experience.%26quot%3B%20Princeton%20has%20also%20vowed%20to%20fight%20racial%20inequity%20and%20has%20published%20diversity%20and%20bias%20reports%20on%20its%20progress%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years.%20But%20the%20persistence%20of%20legacy%20preference%20contradicts%20those%20efforts.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20anti-social%20mobility%2C%26quot%3B%20Murphy%20said.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20if%20social%20mobility%20means%20college%20transforms%20you%20and%20you%20move%20up%20the%20income%20spectrum%2C%20if%20you're%20enrolling%20students%20coming%20from%20the%20richest%20homes%20in%20America%20or%20the%20richest%20households%20in%20America%2C%20then%20you're%20not%20having%20any%20impact%20on%20social%20mobility%20at%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20tide%20may%20finally%20be%20shifting%20against%20legacy%20admissions%2C%20once%20and%20for%20all.%20Since%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20decision%2C%20colleges%20have%20been%20removing%20the%20practice.%20When%20Wesleyan%20announced%20it%20was%20dropping%20legacy%20admissions%20Roth%20was%20adamant%20that%20it%20was%20the%20right%20move.%20%26quot%3BWe%20still%20value%20the%20ongoing%20relationships%20that%20come%20from%20multi-generational%20Wesleyan%20attendance%2C%20but%20there%20will%20be%20no%20'bump'%20in%20the%20selection%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20in%20an%20open%20letter.%20%26quot%3BAs%20has%20been%20almost%20always%20the%20case%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20family%20members%20of%20alumni%20will%20be%20admitted%20on%20their%20own%20merits.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20schools%20like%20Carnegie%20Mellon%20and%20Occidental%20College%20did%20the%20same%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20decision.%20Still%2C%20it's%20unclear%20whether%20prestigious%20schools%20like%20Harvard%20will%20follow%20suit%20in%20ending%20a%20practice%20that%20Kahlenberg%20called%C2%A0%20%26quot%3Bin%20many%20ways%2C%20deeply%20un-American%2C%26quot%3B%20given%20that%2C%20in%20his%20view%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20idea%20of%20America%20was%20to%20get%20away%20from%20hereditary%20privilege%20and%20aristocracy.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20embarrassing%20for%20institutions%2C%20especially%20now%2C%20because%20they%20take%20a%20very%20high%20moral%20posture%20and%20say%2C%20'Racial%20diversity%20is%20essential%20to%20our%20existence%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3B'We%20cannot%20provide%20an%20excellent%20education%20without%20it.'%20But%20if%20they're%20serious%20about%20that%2C%20the%20easiest%20and%20most%20straightforward%20thing%20to%20do%20is%20to%20eliminate%20preferences%20that%20disproportionately%20benefit%20wealthy%20white%20students.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMurphy%20said%20that%20he%20felt%20optimistic%20more%20colleges%20would%20ditch%20the%20practice%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that%20it's%20all%20about%20convincing%20the%20boards%20of%20trustees%20at%20private%20schools%20that%20%26quot%3Bare%20typically%20made%20up%20of%20very%20wealthy%20people%26quot%3B%20who%20stand%20to%20benefit%20the%20most%20from%20legacy%20preferences.%20%26quot%3BI%20remain%20very%20optimistic%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat%20in%20two%20years%20time%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20an%20incredibly%20rare%20practice%20and%20we're%20going%20to%20look%20back%20and%20say%2C%20'What%20were%20we%20ever%20thinking%20as%20a%20country%20that%20we%20ever%20allowed%20this%20to%20go%20on%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fayelet-sheffey%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%2233c4ee918afc4fca8c47ebeab08d18cb%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fayelet-sheffey%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%3EAyelet%20Sheffey%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20senior%20economic%20policy%20reporter%20covering%20student%20debt%20on%20Insider's%20economy%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-elite-colleges-legacy-admissions-financial-endowments-alumni-donations-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696845482000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f250671b7ced0019c72e63%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-elite-colleges-legacy-admissions-financial-endowments-alumni-donations-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Elite%20colleges%20like%20Harvard%20have%20a%20not-so-secret%20reason%20for%20giving%20alumni's%20kids%20special%20treatment%3A%20money.%20But%20it's%20actually%20a%20big%20mistake.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A36%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2F