ort%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222860%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22meta%20AI%20assistants%20caurosel%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651480c81c099d0019ad4858%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221594%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMeta's%20AI%20assistants%20will%20be%20able%20to%20act%20as%20an%20older%20sister%2C%20opinionated%20sports%20debater%2C%20and%20a%20golf%20instructor.%20%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Meta.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMeta%20unveiled%20its%20AI%20assistant%20feature%20last%20month%2C%20featuring%20celebrities'%20likenesses.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EKendall%20Jenner%20and%20MrBeast%20are%20among%20the%20stars%20who%20portray%20Meta's%20chatbots%20with%20different%20personalities.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOne%20unnamed%20top%20creator%20was%20paid%20%245%20million%20for%20six%20hours%20of%20work%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Information.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20is%20paying%20one%20top%20creator%20as%20much%20as%20%245%20million%20over%20two%20years%20for%20six%20hours%20of%20work%20in%20a%20studio%20to%20use%20their%20likeness%20as%20an%20AI%20assistant%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D5a143c235343305a9d92293b4fa90a9b5a338343d24cae824f4f77e4e80d3591%26postID%3D6523bf8b385cb39dead7e848%26postSlug%3Dmeta-paying-celebrity-faces-of-ai-chatbots-as-much-as-5-million-2023-10%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.theinformation.com%252Farticles%252Fmeta-is-paying-creators-millions-for-ai-chatbots%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Information%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-ai-chatbots-assistants-tom-brady-mr-beast-kendall-jenner-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMark%20Zuckerberg%20unveiled%20the%20AI%20assistants%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20the%20company's%20Connect%20event%20last%20month.%20While%20the%20company%20has%20its%20own%20AI%20chatbot%20similar%20to%20ChatGPT%2C%20it%20also%20introduced%2028%20new%20ones%20with%20different%20personalities%20that%20use%20celebrities'%20images.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Kendall%20Jenner's%20likeness%20is%20used%20for%20Billie%2C%20who%20is%20portrayed%20as%20a%20big%20sister%20to%20give%20users%20advice.%20And%20Tom%20Brady%20plays%20Bru%2C%20a%20chatbot%20for%20debating%20sports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20has%20also%20brought%20onboard%20creators%20like%20MrBeast%2C%20the%20most-subscribed%20individual%20on%20YouTube%2C%20and%20the%20TikTok%20star%20Charli%20D'Amelio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Information%20reports%20that%20Meta%20was%20initially%20willing%20to%20pay%20more%20than%20%241%20million%20to%20use%20the%20stars'%20likenesses%2C%20but%20shelled%20out%20more%20for%20big%20names.%20The%20report%20doesn't%20say%20which%20person%20was%20paid%20%245%20million%2C%20but%20primarily%20refers%20to%20creators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20the%20AI%20assistants%20are%20only%20text-based%20but%20Meta's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DqFUc7Y0uSdY%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannouncement%20video%3C%2Fa%3E%20featured%20clips%20of%20the%20celebrities%20speaking%20as%20their%20AI%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20The%20Verge%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-ai-celebrities-fans-next-year-meta-connect-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZuckerberg%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20there's%20a%20%26quot%3Bhuge%20need%26quot%3B%20for%20AI%20versions%20of%20celebrities.%20Although%20he%20said%20that%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bmore%20of%20a%20next%20year%20thing%26quot%3B%20due%20to%20brand%20safety%20concerns%2C%20because%20celebrities%20would%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20their%20image%20won't%20be%20used%20to%20make%20problematic%20statements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%20as%20its%20AI%20assistants%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-new-ai-generated-stickers-inappropriate-content-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%20also%20launched%20AI%20stickers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20that%20feature%20has%20come%20under%20criticism%20as%20users%20have%20managed%20to%20generate%20wild%20images%20like%20a%20child%20soldier%20and%20a%20lewd%20image%20of%20Justin%20Trudeau.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-paying-celebrity-faces-of-ai-chatbots-as-much-as-5-million-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696845201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6523c8d36561dd877e745bac%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-paying-celebrity-faces-of-ai-chatbots-as-much-as-5-million-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Meta%20has%20enlisted%2028%20celebrities%20to%20play%20AI%20chatbots%20with%20different%20personalities.%20One%20top%20creator%20was%20paid%20%245%20million%2C%20per%20The%20Information.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22psyme%40insider.com%20(Pete%20Syme)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A53%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-paying-celebrity-faces-of-ai-chatbots-as-much-as-5-million-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nobel%20prize%20in%20Economic%20Sciences%20awarded%20to%20Claudia%20Goldin%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696844994000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104282629%2Cimgsize-1077709.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2F2023-nobel-prize-in-economic-sciences-awarded-to-claudia-goldin%2Farticleshow%2F104282308.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Claudia%20Goldin%20has%20been%20awarded%20the%202023%20Nobel%