%20Editor%2C%20HR%20Head%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F09132731%2Fnewsclick.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Delhi%20high%20court%20on%20Monday%20(October%209)%20reserved%20its%20judgment%20in%20the%20pleas%20filed%20by%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%20founding%20editor%20Prabir%20Purkayastha%20and%20HR%20head%20Amit%20Chakraborty%20challenging%20the%20remand%20order%20issued%20after%20their%20arrest.%20The%20two%20were%20arrested%20on%20October%203%20in%20relation%20to%20an%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPurkayastha%20and%20Chakraborty%20have%20also%20challenged%20the%20FIR%20against%20them%2C%20and%20the%20judge%20will%20decide%20if%20notice%20is%20to%20be%20sent%20to%20the%20Delhi%20Police%20on%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Tushar%20Rao%20Gedela%20reserved%20the%20judgment%20after%20hearing%20both%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20counsel%20and%20the%20Delhi%20Police%E2%80%99s%20lawyer.%20Solicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%20appeared%20for%20the%20Delhi%20Police.%3Cb%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EArguing%20for%20Purkayastha%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Kapil%20Sibal%20said%20that%20the%20grounds%20of%20arrest%20were%20not%20provided%20at%20the%20time%20of%20arrest%20or%20even%20in%20the%20remand%20order%2C%20thus%20going%20against%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20order%20on%20arrests.%20The%20editor%20was%20also%20not%20allowed%20to%20have%20a%20lawyer%20of%20his%20choice%20present%20during%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20remand%20order%2C%20it%20was%20argued.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESibal%20also%20stated%20that%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20a%20rupee%2C%20not%20a%20penny%E2%80%9D%20had%20come%20from%20China%20to%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20Purkayastha.%20The%20Delhi%20Police%20FIR%20%E2%80%93%20which%20casts%20a%20wide%20net%2C%20ranging%20from%20Chinese%20phone%20producers%20to%20lawyers%20to%20protesting%